# Infrastructure ({{ project_name }})

This component provisions a local Cardano infrastructure stack using
[`cardano-up`](https://github.com/blinklabs-io/cardano-up). The providers you
selected are managed together as a single cardano-up **context** named
`{{ infra_context_name }}` (network: `{{ network }}`):

{% for t in infra_tools %}- **{{ t.tool_name }}** — cardano-up package `{{ t.cardano_up_package }}`
{% endfor %}
## Prerequisites

- **Docker** running.
- **`cardano-up`** on your `PATH` — run `cardano-init doctor` for install help.

## Usage

```sh
just -f infra/Justfile dev      # provision the stack and write ../.env (long-running)
just -f infra/Justfile clean    # stop the stack (chain data is preserved)
```

`dev` creates/uses the `{{ infra_context_name }}` context, installs the
providers (cardano-up resolves dependencies such as `cardano-node`
automatically), brings the Docker services up, and writes the connection
details into the project's `../.env`. Off-chain components read those values
(`INDEXER_URL`, `OGMIOS_URL`, `NODE_SOCKET_PATH`, …) and connect automatically.

The `-c/--context` flag scopes every command to this project's stack, so it
never disturbs your global active cardano-up context or other projects.

## Notes

- This component aggregates **all** `--infra` providers into one stack; there is
  no per-provider subdirectory.
- `cardano-up`'s state is machine-global (under `~/.config/cardano-up` and
  `~/.local/share/cardano-up`), not stored in this repo. The Justfile here is
  just a thin, project-scoped driver over it.
